Cloud Financial Management, often referred to as FinOps, helps organizations balance cloud spending with business value.

Key activities include:

* Budget planning
* Cost forecasting
* Resource optimization
* Chargeback and showback
* Spending analysis
* Financial reporting

For example, development resources can automatically shut down after business hours to reduce unnecessary compute costs.

A real-life use case is organizations reviewing monthly Azure spending to identify unused resources and optimize future budgets.

Effective financial management ensures sustainable cloud adoption without unexpected expenses.
